---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
import Disclaimer from '../../components/Disclaimer.astro'
import VerifyBadge from '../../components/VerifyBadge.astro'
import RedditFeed from '../../components/RedditFeed.astro'
import movePosts from '../../data/reddit-seed/move.json'
---

<Base
  title="Moving to Bermuda"
  description="The honest guide to moving to Bermuda. Work permits, cost of living, immigration pathways, the one-car rule, and what salary you actually need. Real information, not brochure copy."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero" style="padding-block: var(--space-16);">
    <div class="hero__inner">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="breadcrumb" style="justify-content: center; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">
          <li><a href="/Pilot.BM/" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">Home</a></li>
          <li class="breadcrumb__sep" aria-hidden="true">›</li>
          <li style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9);">Moving</li>
        </ol>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Moving to Bermuda</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        The information you need before you commit — not after.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container" style="padding-block: var(--space-12);">

    <!-- Disclaimer — REQUIRED above the fold on all /move/* pages -->
    <Disclaimer variant="immigration" />

    <!-- Key facts -->
    <div style="background-color: var(--color-sand); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-8); margin-bottom: var(--space-10);">
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">What you need to know upfront</h2>
      <div class="card-grid card-grid-2">
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ocean); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Work permit required</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); margin: 0;">
            All non-Bermudians (and non-spouses of Bermudians) need an employer-sponsored work permit.
            No job offer = no legal path to move. The employer must first advertise and show no qualified Bermudian was available.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: #dc2626; margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">
            Work From Bermuda: CLOSED
            <span class="badge badge-closed" style="margin-left: var(--space-2);">Closed 28 Feb 2025</span>
          </h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); margin: 0;">
            The Work From Bermuda digital-nomad programme closed permanently on 28 February 2025.
            It is no longer available. Verify at <a href="https://www.gov.bm" rel="noopener" target="_blank">gov.bm</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ocean); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Cost of living</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); margin: 0;">
            Bermuda's cost of living is approximately <strong>94% above the US average</strong>.
            Rent alone runs ~186% above US norms. Budget accordingly.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ocean); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Mandatory health insurance</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); margin: 0;">
            The Standard Health Benefit (SHB) is mandatory for all residents.
            Current rate: <strong>$400.31/adult/month</strong>.
            <VerifyBadge date="2026-06-10" sourceLabel="Bermuda Health Council" sourceUrl="https://www.bhec.bm" />
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Section nav -->
    <h2 style="margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">The Bermuda moving guide</h2>

    <div class="card-grid card-grid-3">
      <a href="/Pilot.BM/move/work-permit" class="link-card">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Step 1</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">Work Permits</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          How employer sponsorship works. What the employer must do.
          EIRC for investors. Fees and timelines.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/Pilot.BM/move/cost-of-living" class="link-card">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Step 2</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">Cost of Living</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          Rent, groceries, health insurance, school fees, car import duty.
          All figures with sources. What salary actually buys you here.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/Pilot.BM/move/tools/pathway" class="link-card link-card--featured">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">★ Tool</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">Immigration Pathway Finder</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          Do you even qualify to move? Answer three questions and find out which pathway —
          if any — applies to you.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/Pilot.BM/move/tools/assessment-number" class="link-card">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">★ Tool</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">The Car Trap</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          One car per household. Assessment Numbers explained. This surprises almost every mover.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/Pilot.BM/move/tools/compensation" class="link-card">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Calculator (Beta)</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">Compensation Calculator</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          What salary do you need in Bermuda to match your current lifestyle?
          Calculates required gross based on rent, family size, school, and health insurance.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/Pilot.BM/move/healthcare" class="link-card">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Healthcare</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">Healthcare in Bermuda</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          The Standard Health Benefit (SHB) is mandatory from day one. What it covers, what it doesn't,
          and how employer plans typically top it up.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/Pilot.BM/move/schools" class="link-card">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Schools</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">Schools Guide</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          Saltus, BHS, Warwick Academy, The Bermuda Institute — fees, curricula, and how
          early to apply. Apply before you've confirmed the move.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/Pilot.BM/move/banking" class="link-card">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Banking</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">Banking for Expats</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          Butterfield Bank, HSBC Bermuda, Clarien. Account opening takes 2–4 weeks.
          Monthly fees apply. US investment account restrictions to know about.
        </p>
      </a>

      <a href="/Pilot.BM/directory" class="link-card">
        <p class="link-card__eyebrow">Directory</p>
        <h3 class="link-card__title">Movers Directory</h3>
        <p class="link-card__desc">
          Real estate agents, international movers, insurance brokers, relocation consultants —
          curated for people making the move.
        </p>
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Honest summary -->
    <div style="margin-top: var(--space-12); padding: var(--space-8); background-color: var(--color-ocean-muted); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">The honest summary</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
        Moving to Bermuda is a serious commitment. The pathway requires employer sponsorship —
        there is no "move first, find work later" option unless you qualify for the EIRC investor
        certificate ($2.5M minimum investment). The cost of living is genuinely higher than almost
        anywhere else in the world.
      </p>
      <p style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
        For the right person in the right role, it's an extraordinary place to live —
        safe, beautiful, and with a tight-knit expat community. The international business sector
        (insurance, reinsurance, asset management) compensates accordingly.
      </p>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin: 0;">
        This guide is for general information only. Verify everything at <a href="https://www.gov.bm" rel="noopener" target="_blank">gov.bm</a>
        and consult a Bermuda immigration attorney for your specific situation.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <RedditFeed posts={movePosts} />
</Base>
